Compare Variant Callers

C. Savonen for ALSF CCDL

2019

Purpose: After running the initial analyses of each variant caller, this notebook combines the output from those calculations and compares them.

Usage

To run this from the command line, use:

Rscript -e "rmarkdown::render('analyses/tmb-calculations/compare_variant_callers.Rmd', 
                              clean = TRUE)"

This assumes you are in the top directory of the repository.

Setup

Packages and functions

Read in set up script.

if (!("ggupset" %in% installed.packages())) {
  install.packages("ggupset", repos='http://cran.us.r-project.org')
}
if (!("UpSetR" %in% installed.packages())) {
  install.packages("UpSetR", repos='http://cran.us.r-project.org')
}
if (!("GGally" %in% installed.packages())) {
  install.packages("GGally", repos='http://cran.us.r-project.org')
}

Set up output directories.

base_results_dir <- "results"
base_plots_dir <- "plots"

Make new directories for the comparison analysis.

compare_results_dir <- file.path(base_results_dir, "comparisons")
compare_plots_dir <- file.path(base_plots_dir, "comparisons")

# Make caller specific plots folder
if (!dir.exists(compare_results_dir)) {
  dir.create(compare_results_dir)
}
# Make caller specific plots folder
if (!dir.exists(compare_plots_dir)) {
  dir.create(compare_plots_dir)
}

Import data

dir(base_results_dir)
[1] "comparisons" "lancet"      "mutect2"     "strelka2"    "vardict"

Get the lists of each type of file.

# Get the lists of each type of file
vaf_files <- list.files(base_results_dir, pattern = "_vaf.tsv$", recursive = TRUE, 
                        full.names = TRUE) 
tmb_files <- list.files(base_results_dir, pattern = "_tmb.tsv$", recursive = TRUE, 
                        full.names = TRUE) 
region_annot_files <- list.files(base_results_dir, pattern = "_region.tsv$", recursive = TRUE, 
                        full.names = TRUE) 
# Get the caller names
caller_names <- stringr::word(vaf_files, sep = "/", 2)

Make a big VAF data.frame

vaf_list <- lapply(vaf_files, function(file) {
  readr::read_tsv(file) %>%
    dplyr::select("mutation_id", "vaf", "base_change", "change")

Upsett graph

mutation_id_list <- lapply(vaf_list, function(caller) caller$mutation_id)

UpSetR::upset(UpSetR::fromList(mutation_id_list), order.by = "freq")

Graph mutations by combinations of callers and plot the VAF density.

callers_per_mutation <- vaf_df %>% 
  dplyr::select(mutation_id, caller) %>% 
  reshape2::melt() %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(mutation_id) %>% 
  dplyr::summarize(callers = paste0(caller, collapse = "-"),
                   med_vaf = median(vaf))

callers_per_mutation %>%
  ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x = callers, y = med_vaf)) +
  ggplot2::geom_violin() +
  ggupset::scale_x_mergelist(sep = "-") +
  ggupset::axis_combmatrix(sep = "-")

Base Changes

region_annot_df %>% 
  dplyr::group_by(change, caller) %>% 
  dplyr::summarize(count = dplyr::n()) %>%
  ggplot2::ggplot(ggplot2::aes(x = change, y = count)) + 
  ggplot2::theme_classic() + 
  ggplot2::geom_bar(position = "dodge", stat = "identity",
        ggplot2::aes(fill = caller)) + 
  ggplot2::theme(axis.text.x = ggplot2::element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  ggplot2::xlab("") +
  ggplot2::ylab("Count") +
  colorblindr::scale_fill_OkabeIto()

VAF distributions
